    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="1396"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1396">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/266.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Spanish Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Spanish Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 10, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: With reference to previous
                    correspondence, I beg to inform you that Sr. Armendaiz telegraphs me under the
                    date of the 9th instant, that the Constitutionalists at Monterey have forced the
                    representative of his firm in that town to <pb facs="0926" n="810"
                        xml:id="pg_810"/> give them a draft of $12,000 on Sr. Armendaiz, and if this
                    draft is not paid the agent will be put in the penitentiary.</p>
                <p>I beg to call your attention once more to this case, and to request you with the
                    utmost earnestness to exert your influence with the Constitutionalists to avoid
                    this robbery with which Mr. Armendaiz is menaced.</p>
                <p>Believe me [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Juan Riaño</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
